\series bold 
Activity 3: Two Coils and a Varying Current
\layout Enumerate

With the large coil laying flat on the table, place the small coil at its
 center so that the axes of the coils coincide.
 Be sure no magnets are near either coil.
\layout Enumerate

Set the signal generator FREQUENCY knob to the 2K-20K position and the frequency
 dial to 40.
 In other words, set the frequency to 4 kHz.
 Set the function switch to SINE, the OUTPUT (VOLT P-P) RANGE knob at 10
 and the LEVEL knob at mid-range.
 Turn on the generator
\layout Enumerate

Run the VI.
 Two sine curves will be displayed: the red one is the voltage signal being
 supplied to the large coil by the generator.
 The blue curve is the emf induced in the small coil by the varying current
 in the large coil.
 Note the amplitude of the induced current and the phase relationship between
 the two curves.
 Ypu may have to adjust the number of scans and scan rate to get good traces
 of the signals.
